From: Kairo RFC/POC <local@kairo.invalid>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [RFC/POC] mq-deadline: add experimental Kairo decode-read priority

This local RFC/POC patch sketches the first Kairo scheduler experiment:
classify decode-critical KV-cache reads using existing ioprio metadata and
prefer them in mq-deadline dispatch before lower-priority background traffic.

This is not intended for LKML submission. The ioprio mapping is an internal
prototype signal, not a permanent UAPI.

Temporary classification:

  IOPRIO_CLASS_RT, prio 0, READ  -> KAIRO_DECODE_READ
  IOPRIO_CLASS_RT, prio 1, READ  -> KAIRO_PREFETCH_READ
  IOPRIO_CLASS_BE, prio 7, WRITE -> KAIRO_PREFILL_WRITE

The exact insertion points may need adjustment for the target kernel version.
---
 block/mq-deadline.c | 64 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 64 insertions(+)

diff --git a/block/mq-deadline.c b/block/mq-deadline.c
index 000000000000..111111111111 100644
--- a/block/mq-deadline.c
+++ b/block/mq-deadline.c
@@ -1,3 +1,67 @@
+/*
+ * Kairo RFC/POC notes:
+ *
+ * This patch is intentionally scaffold-level. It documents the local
+ * scheduler logic to be wired into mq-deadline on the target kernel tree.
+ * The final placement depends on the exact Linux version being patched.
+ */
+
+#include <linux/ioprio.h>
+
+static bool kairo_enable = true;
+static unsigned int kairo_decode_budget = 32;
+
+static inline bool dd_kairo_is_decode_read(struct request *rq)
+{
+	unsigned short ioprio = req_get_ioprio(rq);
+
+	return rq_data_dir(rq) == READ &&
+	       IOPRIO_PRIO_CLASS(ioprio) == IOPRIO_CLASS_RT &&
+	       IOPRIO_PRIO_DATA(ioprio) == 0;
+}
+
+static inline bool dd_kairo_is_prefetch_read(struct request *rq)
+{
+	unsigned short ioprio = req_get_ioprio(rq);
+
+	return rq_data_dir(rq) == READ &&
+	       IOPRIO_PRIO_CLASS(ioprio) == IOPRIO_CLASS_RT &&
+	       IOPRIO_PRIO_DATA(ioprio) == 1;
+}
+
+static inline bool dd_kairo_is_prefill_write(struct request *rq)
+{
+	unsigned short ioprio = req_get_ioprio(rq);
+
+	return rq_data_dir(rq) == WRITE &&
+	       IOPRIO_PRIO_CLASS(ioprio) == IOPRIO_CLASS_BE &&
+	       IOPRIO_PRIO_DATA(ioprio) == 7;
+}
+
+/*
+ * Intended dispatch policy:
+ *
+ * 1. If Kairo mode is disabled, preserve existing mq-deadline behavior.
+ * 2. If a decode-critical read exists and decode budget remains, dispatch it.
+ * 3. If prefetch reads are approaching deadline, prefer them after decode.
+ * 4. Fall back to existing mq-deadline read/write logic.
+ * 5. Preserve write progress with starvation/deadline escape behavior.
+ *
+ * Pseudocode insertion point inside the mq-deadline dispatch function:
+ *
+ *   if (kairo_enable) {
+ *       rq = dd_kairo_next_decode_read(dd);
+ *       if (rq && dd->kairo_decode_dispatches < kairo_decode_budget)
+ *           return dd_dispatch_request(q, rq);
+ *   }
+ *
+ * TODO:
+ * - Add a real decode-read lane or tree scan based on target mq-deadline code.
+ * - Add starvation accounting.
+ * - Add sysfs/debugfs stats.
+ * - Reset decode budget per dispatch epoch.
+ */
+
 /* existing mq-deadline code continues below in the target kernel tree */
